{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015h1TNDJAXF4GG9smxBdPas","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So rabbitmq-0 has stopped (the log shows it stopped). This might be because the StatefulSet was scaled to 1, but when the cluster tried to scale down from 3 to 1, it stopped rabbitmq-0 as part of the process? Actually, wait - the StatefulSet has replicas: 1, but the readout showed:\n\n```\nstatefulset.apps/rabbitmq   2/1     100s\n```\n\nThis means 2 pods are still running (ready) but only 1 is desired. Since rabbitmq-1 is Terminating, the cluster is being scaled from 2 down to 1, with rabbitmq-0 being the remaining pod.\nBut looking at the pod status more carefully, rabbitmq-0 shows as Running with 1/1 ready, yet the logs indicate the RabbitMQ application inside it has stopped - which is strange. The logs mention \"Successfully stopped RabbitMQ and its dependencies,\" so maybe this is a recent shutdown event that hasn't fully propagated yet.\n\nThere's a contradiction here: if the readiness probe is passing (which would require the rabbit app to be running), then the app should be active. Unless there's a race condition where it was running during the probe check but has since stopped. I'm wondering if the cluster scaling down from 3 to 1 node has put the remaining node into an inconsistent state, possibly losing quorum or cluster membership.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3118,"cache_read_input_tokens":31452,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3118},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b50b2ae1-7fa0-4cbf-997c-51c910a1a7d7","uuid":"5496707a-0a07-4a5f-a242-b7ce47e23017","request_id":"req_011CccYz9U2zy5YhB6Wzwfxd"}
